/*
 * $Id: ChangeLog,v 1.1083 2003/05/29 22:54:57 paultucker Exp $
 */

/* Use this format for the entry headers:
   YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM UTC[-|+]hhmm Your Full Name <your_email@address>
   For example:
   2002-12-01 23:12 UTC+0100 Foo Bar <foo.bar@foobar.org>
*/

2003-05-29 18:50 UTC-0500 Paul Tucker <ptucker@sympatico.ca>
  * include/hbtrac.h
  * source/rtl/trace.c
    * removed my changes till I can better see what's wrong

2003-05-29 15:30 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * source/rtl/trace.c
    - Uncommented code to create "trace.log" file and changed logic to reset the file if it exists.
  * source/rtl/traceprg.prg
    + Added logic to create Trace File if missing.
    * Refnied output format.

  * tests/pp.prg
    + Added logic to Save s_bArrayPrefix before calls to MatchRule() and Restore it if it failed.
    ! Fixed #translate rule for At( <what>, <where>, <from> ) for Clipper.
    ! Fixed NextToken() (prg version) handling of '' strings.
    ! Fixed #include logic to NOT conver filename to uppercase.
    + Added burned-in rules for "rp_dot.ch"
    + Added logic to use burned-in rules UNLESS "rp_dot.ch" is persent.

    /* pp once again functional when compiled with Clipper. */

  * tests/pp_harb.ch
    + Added SetArrayPrefix() interface.

2003-05-29 22:40 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak <druzus@polbox.com>
  * xharbour/tests/pp.prg
    * some additional modification for running .prg files as script
      and to make pp working on *nix systems - '/' as as directory
      delimiter, ':' as a path separator
      _DEFAULT_INC_DIR macro added and passing parameters to .prg
      if pp is called pprun - now you can create a link 'pprun' to 'pp'
      and use it as a script interpreter.
      Ron, I hope I didn't break anything in PP with these changes.

  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtnul/gtnul.c
  * xharbour/xharbour.spec
    + new binary RPM with Ron's PP
    + new tools: xhbcc, xhbcmp, xhblnk and xhbmk, now you can
      specify GT during linking time by -gt<name> option. You don't
      have to add REQUEST HB_GT_<name> to your source code. The
      fallowing switches can be used:
        -o<outputfilename> # output file name
        -static         # link with static libs
        -shared         # link with shared libs (default)
        -mt             # link with multi-thread libs
        -gt<hbgt>       # link with <hbgt> GT driver, can be repeated to
                        # link with more GTs. The first one will be default
                        # on runtime

  * xharbour/include/hbextern.ch
    * some functions added to use it with PP
      I think the files wasn't updated for a long time. Maybe
      developers should add their new functions to them.

  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtcrs/gtcrs.c
    * some keys for XTERM4 added.

  * xharbour/source/rtl/trace.c
    * commented out the code which makes empty trace.log file if you
      run program linked with TRACELOG function. I have too many such
      empty files on my disk :-( - is it really necessary.

2003-05-28 26:20 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * tests/pp.prg
    ! Fixed minor bug in CompilDefine() which mistakenly treated parentesized expression as a Psedu-Function.
    * Changed default action to RUN [-R] when Source File argument supplied (unless -P switch present).
    + Added support for Linux Type Association <#!> (guarded with #ifdef __PLATFORM_Linux).

