2003-05-27 20:56 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  + include/hbvmprv.h
    + New header for definitions NOT shared with the Compiler.
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    - Removed definition for SYMBOLS and replace with #include "hbvmprv.h"
  * source/vm/runner.c
    - Removed duplicate definition for SYMBOLS and replace with #include "hbvmprv.h"

  * include/classes.h
    + Added Member PHB_SYMB pModuleSymbols to CLASS Structure.

  * include/hbexprb.c
  * include/hbpcode.h
  * source/compiler/genc.c
  * source/compiler/hbfix.c
  * source/compiler/hbpcode.c
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + Added support for new Pseudo Function __ClsSetModule() as new PCODE HB_P_CLASSSETMODULE

  * include/hbclass.ch
    ! Optimized Instantiation.
    + Added support for new __ClsSetModule()

  * source/vm/classes.c
    + Added logic to utilize new pModuleSymbols Member of CLASS Structure to accept SAME MODULE access to ANY SCOPE.

  * tests/tstscope.prg
  + tests/scope1.prg
  + tests/scope2.prg
    * Modified to show Scoping Validation of MULTI-MODULE inter-crossed with INHERITANCE.
    /* Use:
         bld_b32 tstscope scope1 scope2
         bld_vc  tstscope scope1 scope2
    */

  * bin/bld.bat
    * Modified to allow 3 sources to be compiled and linked.

 /*
    NOTE: Finally we should have FULL SUPPORT for OOP Scoping as per standards established by current
          Leading Tools.

          As you may know, we never had support for a Module [Unit of compilation] scoping. This was
          a serious omission, and was a BIG hurdle in correctly addressing SCOPE problems with WHOO
          [and likely many other projects]. Well now xHarbour fully support compilation unit scoping
          so that when you have multiple classes that need access to PROTECTED Members of each other
          you may now place those classes in the SAME Module, and avoid the SCOPE issues that you'd
          otherwise encounter [unless you'd dismissed the required restricted SCOPEing. altogether.]
 */
