2003-05-27 22:07 UTC+0200 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/rtl/regex.c
    + Added HB_RegexAtx() function. It has the same grammar as
      HB_Regex, but it merges the functionality of Regex and Atx:
      the returned array is itself made of arrays containing the
      matched string, the start position of the match in the
      source string, and the end position. An entry is for the
      whole match, and the following are for the subgroups matches.

      The returned array has the form:
      { {WholeMatch, nStartWhole, nEndWhole },
        {Group1, nStartGroup1, nEndGroup1 },
        ...
        {GroupN, nStartGroupn, nEndGroupN }
      }
      ( for who does not remember, a "group" is an expression
        between parenthesis in a regex search pattern)
      RFC: the end position may be obtained with Len() + nStart
      but it seems to me it would be less efficient.

  * tests/regex.prg
    + Added a test for HB_RegexAtx()

2003-05-27 16:50 UTC-0300 Walter Negro <anegro@overnet.com.ar>
  * source/rtl/tbrowse.prg
    ! Fix logic to repositioning after to gobottom().
      Reported by Oscar Hernandez Suarez
    ! Evaluate skipblock with 0 in goto() for compatibilit with Clipper.
      Report and code provided by Oscar Hernandez Suarez

