2003-05-25 19:08 UTC+0200 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/fm.c
    ! using now hb_allocMutex to threadsafe statistics also when
      HB_SAFE_ALLOC is on.

  * include/thread.h
  * source/vm/thread.c
  * source/vm/estack.c
    + Added support for macro and try/catch blocks under MT. - mainly
      is an issue related with thread specific error block (or error
      management).
    + Added hb_macroMutex to mutex macro compilation, that is thread
      unsafe.

  * source/macro/macro.y
    ! macro compilation is now subject to mutexing, as it uses
      static variables that are not thread safe. This is a limit
      in bison/ylex, and there is nothing we can do about it.

  * source/rtl/terror.prg
  * source/rtl/errorsys.prg
    + Added thread specific error management
    + Added thread specific fields for error reporting.

  * include/hbapierr.h
  * source/vm/errorapi.c
    + Added functions to access (put/get) directly thread related members
      in tError

  * source/vm/arrays.c
    - remove old comments.

