  * xharbour/source/rtl/gt_tpl/gt_tpl.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gt_tpl/mousetpl.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtcgi/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtcgi/gtcgi.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtcgi/mousecgi.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtcrs/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtcrs/gtcrs.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtcrs/gtcrs.h
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtdos/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtdos/gtdos.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtdos/mousedos.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtos2/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtos2/gtos2.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtos2/mouseos2.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtpca/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtpca/gtpca.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtpca/kbdos2.gcc
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtpca/mousepca.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtsln/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtsln/gtsln.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtsln/gtsln.h
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtsln/kbsln.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtsln/keytrans.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtsln/mousesln.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtsln/termtype.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtstd/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtstd/gtstd.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtstd/mousestd.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwin/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwin/gtwin.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwin/mousewin.c
    + New MULTI GT mode added. Now you can link your applications with
      more then one GT and choose it at runtime by switch //GT:<gtname>
      ex.:
        ./myprog //gt:sln
        ./myprog //gt:crs
        ./myprog //gt:pca
        ./myprog //gt:nul
      or by setting environment variables HB_GT=<gtname>
      to make xHarbour binaries with MULTI GT you have to set environment
      variable HB_MULTI_GT=yes
      then if you link your apps with static libraries you always have to
      link with gtnul and optionally with other gt libs you need.
      GTNUL is basic lib. It has to have all GT features. Other GTs may
      not have all function implemented on some platforms. My main idea
      was to allow developers adding platform specific GT extension without
      necessary of changing all GTs.
      I've tested it under Linux and it works correctly for:
      gtcrs, gtsln, gtpca, gtstd, gtcgi and gtnul (gt_tpl too ;-)).
      I added support for MULTI GT for gtwin too, but it has to be checked
      by someone who use Windows because now I cannot even compile it
      (I don't have windows access at this moment). I hope it'll work
      but maybe I made some typos.
      TODO:
        add MULTI GT support for gtdos, gtos2 and gtQTc. I have to ask
        developers to do that - it's rather hard for me because I don't
        use this platform. Now all the works is very easy - you only
        have to change all functions with hb_gt_ and hb_mouse_ prefixes
        to HB_GT_FUNC(gt_<...>) and HB_GT_FUNC(mouse_<...>) then
        add initialization code (see tail of gt_tpl.c)
      I've change a lot of code so It have to be intensively tested on
      different platforms.

  * xharbour/source/rtl/seconds.c
    * the symbol CLK_TCK which is mentioned as obsolescent in POSIX-1996
      replaced by sysconf(_SC_CLK_TCK)

  * xharbour/make_gnu.sh
  * xharbour/make_mingw.sh
  * xharbour/bin/!pack_src.bat
  + xharbour/bin/!pack_src.sh
    * some cleanups.

