2003-05-14 10:28 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/errorapi.c
  * include/hbapierr.h
  * source/rtl/terror.prg
    + Added ProcLine and ProcName fields to the tError class; they are
      filled by default with the calling procedure name and line.
    + Added hb_errGetProcName, hb_errPutProcName, hb_errGetProcLine and
      hb_errPutProcLine to access those data from c.
    * In c api error initialization, hb_errPutProcName and hb_errPutProcLine
      are called to set the PRG calling procedure as error proc/line.

  * source/rtl/filesys.c
    ! Under LINUX, Memoread was CREATING an EXECUTABLE empty file if
      the required file was not present on disk. This is due to some
      invalid flags (under linux) used for open() flags. To hot-fix
      this, in convert_open_flags() I used HB_OS_LINUX define to
      exclude those open flags.
      LINUX and other UNIX users are invited to review this.


2003-05-13 14:52 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
