  * source/compiler/genc.c
    ! Corrected genc.c generation of Global Initialization to overcome a GCC warning.

2003-05-12 13:48 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * source/pp/ppcore.c
    ! Fixed getExpReal() to consider operators as Macro terminator.

  * source/vm/hvm.c
    * Corrected hb_vmArrayPush() to return empty string when processing a -1 Index on an Emprt String.
      /*
       * Empty String and Index is -1, this may be result of optimixations:
       *
       *    SubStr( "", -1, 1 ) or aTail( "" ).
       *
       * The SubStr() should return "", while the aTail("") should return NIL (Invalid Argument).
       *
       * We choose the SubStr() context as the more appropriate, because the Invalid Arguemnt context
       * is of questionable compabtibilty value.
       *
       * HBTest now returns 101 "errors" (up from 100) on WinXP using BCC 5.5.1
       */

