      but not under windows).

2003-04-14 01:51 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/inet.c
    ! EAGAIN error (retry later) was handled back to PRG
      program by InetAccept() as any other error, but
      InetAccept() model is made so that a prg can count on
      the facts that InetAccept() returns only if:
      1) there is a REAL error that requires PRG attention
      2) there is a timeout
      3) there is a valid connection
      So EAGAIN is now handled inside InetAccept looping while
      another error or a valid connection is taken.
    ! Now InetAccept returns NIL on failure, and the error is
      stored in the accepting socket.

  * samples/sitesvr/sitesvr.prg
    ! Removed HBConsoleLock() - it is "deprecated"
    ! Changed to reflect new Inet.c InetAccept implementation

  * source/rtl/trpc.prg
  * tests/server.prg
    ! Changed to reflect new Inet.c InetAccept implementation



