2003-04-05 11:58 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * bin/bld.bat
    * Check for existence of bcc640.lib or NOT include it in lib list for bcc32

  * tests/pp.prg
  * tests/pp_harb.ch
    * Removed ?? from list of bi-chars, Clipper treats it as 2 tokens.

  * source/pp/ppcomp.c
  * source/pp/ppcore.c
    + Added hb_pp_NextToken() borrowed from pp.prg.
    ! Complete rewrite of main matching logic to fix long outstanding Clipper compatibility problems.

  /*
     NOTE: I wanted to fix this for the longest time, but for some reason really dreaded it. Pre-Processor
           was seriously NOT Clipper compatible regarding some critical issues that [likely] were not that
           common. But as I feared, with time, I got more and more reports of problems where a complete
           re-write of the matching engine was requires. Here are some of the more obvious examples of
           such problems:

              //---------------------------------------------
              #translate "hello" => Helloed()
              ? "hello"

              #translate KEY SUFFIX <x> => Correct( <x> )
              #translate SUFFIX <x> => Wrong( <x> )
              KEY SUFFIX "indeed"
              //---------------------------------------------

          Of course there were many similar variations. Well now after this rewrite the Pre-Processor should
          be MUCH more Clipper compatible. I've tested the new engine against full build of xHarbour as well
          full build of FiveHX, and many other tests, and all seems to work correctly, BUT since this is a
          major rewrite I'd like all developers to test this with all their applications before we release
          build 0.80.
   */

