2003-03-13 03:58 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * thread.h
    ! fixed linux compilation

2003-03-13 03:50 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * thread.h
  * thread.c
    ! Removed all compiation warnings (tnx Andy ;-)
    + Added async cancelation for threads in the new framework
      under windows.
    * Changed StopThread() behavior: under windows, it kindly
      requests the thread to terminate. Use KillThread() or
      KillAllThreads() to really interrupt a thread, and use
      KillThread( th ) / JoinThread( th ) to kill a thread and
      wait for cleanup functions to be completed. I could port
      this behavior also under linux, but since linux cancelation
      are safe, there is no need for a "kind" StopThread().
      Comments are welcome.

