2003-02-26 15:35 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
   * include/thread.h
   * source/vm/thread.c
     % secured more deeply the thread start process. Now it is secured also
       against memory leaks caused by threads starting other threads but
       being killed in the meanwhile.

   * source/vm/garbage.c
     ! There was a duplicate mutex unlock in the GC collection last steps
       (it was a typo!). This error is ignored under linux but causes
       an immediate deadlock under windows. Now it is gone (and MTGC
       is running fine also on Windows).

2003-02-25 22:43 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * include/hbvmpub.h
    + Added HB_FS_CRITICAL

  * source/compiler/genc.c
  * source/compiler/harbour.slx
  * source/compiler/harbour.sly
    + Added support for NEW Sysntax:
        CRITICAL [STATIC] FUNCTION|PROCEDURE ...
    /*
       The CRITICAL qualifier guarantees that such function can NOT be run by more then 1 Thread
       at a given time. Any other Thread about to start the CRITICAL Function, will be put on hold,
       until the 1st Thread completed execution of the CRITICAL Function.
     */

2003-02-26 07:10 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
   * source/vm/garbage.c
   * source/vm/thread.c
     ! Now compiling on windows

